<p>
<seg id=1> Six Arabic countries in the Gulf, including Syria and Greece, together appealed to Iraq to follow the UN's resolution to allow weapons inspections in order to avoid a confrontation that will only put Iraqi civilian citizens in harms way. </seg>
<seg id=2> The White House welcomed this pronouncement, and regarded this as yet more evidence that the Iraqi leader, Sadam Husin is facing isolation by the world. However, most Iraqis are not worried about the possibility of being bombed by the US and alliance forces. </seg>
